<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="9Jun1927"><font color="red">9 June 1927</font> <i>Beach Letters</i> (to Sylvia Beach): Can E.P.  make the following changes. I cannot page them as I have no proof / Towards the end when <font face="wake">C</font> is supposed to be ejected by the female bar / for &lsquo;Your garbage about our father!&rsquo; read &lsquo;Your guff and your gaff and your garbage about our <i>father!</i>&rsquo; &lsquo;farver!&rsquo; / A little earlier wher <font face="wake">C</font> swears a pagano-Christian oath / for &lsquo;his heroes in Warhorror&rsquo; read &lsquo;our hairoes in Warhorror&rsquo;. &hellip; Yes, I worked many days on the proof and suppose I shall now start on the <i>Criterion</i> piece. </div>
